# D&D 5e SRD Library

A local offline D&D 5e SRD reference app. Available as a **standalone desktop application** (no Python required) for Windows, macOS, and Linux, or runnable directly from source.

---

## Download & Run (desktop app — no Python required)

Pre-built executables are attached to every [GitHub Release](../../releases). Download the file for your platform, then follow the steps below.

### Windows

1. Download `dnd_lib-windows.exe` from the [latest release](../../releases/latest).
2. Double-click to run.
   > Windows Defender / SmartScreen may warn about an unsigned app. Click **"More info" → "Run anyway"** to proceed.
3. A system tray icon (bottom-right) appears. Your browser opens automatically at http://127.0.0.1:5000.
4. To quit, right-click the tray icon → **Quit**.

### macOS

1. Download `dnd_lib-macos` from the [latest release](../../releases/latest).
2. Open a terminal and make it executable:
   ```bash
   chmod +x ~/Downloads/dnd_lib-macos
   ```
3. macOS Gatekeeper blocks unsigned binaries by default. Run it with:
   ```bash
   xattr -d com.apple.quarantine ~/Downloads/dnd_lib-macos
   ~/Downloads/dnd_lib-macos
   ```
   Or go to **System Settings → Privacy & Security** and click **"Open Anyway"** after the first blocked attempt.
4. A tray icon appears in the menu bar. Your browser opens automatically at http://127.0.0.1:5000.
5. To quit, click the tray icon → **Quit**.

### Linux

1. Download `dnd_lib-linux` from the [latest release](../../releases/latest).
2. Make it executable and run:
   ```bash
   chmod +x ~/Downloads/dnd_lib-linux
   ~/Downloads/dnd_lib-linux
   ```
3. A system tray icon appears. Your browser opens automatically at http://127.0.0.1:5000.
4. To quit, right-click the tray icon → **Quit**.

> **Note:** The tray icon requires a desktop environment with a system tray (e.g. GNOME with AppIndicator extension, KDE, XFCE). Headless / Wayland-only setups may need an indicator extension installed.

### Where is my data saved?

Custom items and characters are stored in a writable user-data directory — they persist across updates and are never inside the executable itself:

| Platform | Path |
|---|---|
| Windows | `%APPDATA%\dnd_lib\custom_items.json` |
| macOS | `~/Library/Application Support/dnd_lib/custom_items.json` |
| Linux | `~/.local/share/dnd_lib/custom_items.json` |

---

## Features

- **Offline SRD Browser** — All SRD 2014 category data bundled inside the app
- **D&D-styled cards** — Stat blocks for monsters, spells, equipment, classes, races, and more
- **Search** — Global search bar with optional category filter
- **Category tabs** — Browse items by category with a collapsible sidebar (toggle with ☰)
- **Cross-references** — Clickable links between items open floating popups
- **Multiple cards** — Open several item cards side by side in the main panel
- **Monster spellcasting** — Spells grouped by level with clickable spell links
- **Custom items** — Add custom items to any category via JSON editor; characters use a simplified name/HP/AC form
- **Initiative Tracker** — Right-side panel for combat tracking:
  - Search and add monsters or characters to the initiative table
  - Columns: Initiative, Name, HP, AC, Condition, Notes
  - Click HP to apply damage (subtracted from current HP)
  - Initiative auto-sorts highest first
  - Conditions dropdown with all SRD conditions
  - Panel is resizable by dragging the left edge
- **Dark mode** — Toggle with the 🌙 button; preference saved in the browser
- **JSON viewer** — View raw JSON for any item card
- **System tray** — Runs headlessly; tray icon provides "Open in Browser" and "Quit"

---

## Run from source

### Requirements

- Python 3.10+

### Setup

```bash
git clone <repo-url>
cd dnd_lib
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate        # Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### Development mode (Flask dev server, auto-reload)

```bash
python src/dnd_lib/app.py --dev
```

Open http://127.0.0.1:5000. The `--dev` flag enables Flask debug mode with auto-reload.

### Production mode from source (Waitress + auto-open browser)

```bash
python src/dnd_lib/app.py
```

### Tray runner from source

```bash
PYTHONPATH=src python -m dnd_lib.tray
```

Optional flags for `app.py`:

| Flag | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `--dev` | off | Use Flask dev server instead of Waitress |
| `--host` | `127.0.0.1` | Host to bind to |
| `--port` | `5000` | Port to listen on |

---

## Build the desktop app locally

PyInstaller **cannot cross-compile** — you must build on the target OS.

```bash
# Install build dependencies
pip install -e ".[build]"

# Generate icons (requires Pillow — already in requirements.txt)
python scripts/create_icons.py

# Build single-file executable -> dist/dnd_lib (or dist/dnd_lib.exe on Windows)
python scripts/build.py
```

---

## CI/CD — Automated cross-platform builds

The included [`.github/workflows/build.yml`](.github/workflows/build.yml) builds executables for all three platforms automatically:

- **Trigger:** push a version tag (`v1.0.0`, `v1.2.3`, etc.) or run manually via workflow_dispatch.
- **Matrix:** `windows-latest`, `macos-latest`, `ubuntu-latest` — each builds its own native executable.
- **Artifacts:** uploaded per-run under the Actions tab.
- **Release:** when triggered by a tag, a GitHub Release is created automatically with all three executables attached.

To cut a release:

```bash
git tag v1.0.0
git push origin v1.0.0
```

---

## API Reference

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `GET` | `/api/categories` | List all categories |
| `GET` | `/api/category/<slug>` | List items in a category (supports filter params) |
| `GET` | `/api/category/<slug>/filters` | Available filter options for a category |
| `GET` | `/api/item/<slug>/<item_index>` | Full item data |
| `GET` | `/api/resolve/<item_index>` | Resolve item index to its category |
| `GET` | `/api/search?q=<query>&category=<slug>` | Search across all SRD data |
| `GET` | `/api/initiative-search?q=<query>` | Search monsters and characters |
| `GET` | `/api/global-index` | Full global index for cross-reference resolution |
| `POST` | `/api/custom/<slug>` | Add a custom item (`{name, item}`) |
| `PUT` | `/api/custom/<slug>/<index>` | Update a custom item |
| `DELETE` | `/api/custom/<slug>/<index>` | Delete a custom item |
| `POST` | `/api/character` | Create a character (`{name, hp, ac}`) |

---

## Project structure

```
dnd_lib/
├── .github/workflows/
│   └── build.yml              # CI/CD: cross-platform PyInstaller builds + GitHub Releases
├── data/
│   └── 2014/                  # SRD JSON files (read-only reference data)
├── src/dnd_lib/
│   ├── app.py                 # Flask app, API routes, path resolution
│   ├── tray.py                # Desktop tray runner (pystray + Waitress)
│   ├── static/                # CSS, JS, icons (icon.png, icon.ico)
│   └── templates/             # index.html
├── scripts/
│   ├── build.py               # PyInstaller build helper
│   ├── create_icons.py        # Generates icon.png + icon.ico via Pillow
│   └── migrate_customs.py     # One-time data migration utility
├── dnd_lib.spec               # PyInstaller spec file
├── pyproject.toml             # Project metadata and dependencies
└── requirements.txt           # Runtime dependencies
```

